NAME
lxcu-create -- Create a new lxc container of a certain type.
SYNOPSIS
lxcu-create [OPTIONS]
DESCRIPTION
lxcu-create will create a container of a certain type for a specified
distribution and release. These types specify what extra packages to install or
cache and are specified in the sysconfdir/lxcu directory. The only mandatory
type is 'basic' so this must always be specified.
OPTIONS
-d, --dist 'distribution-name'

-h, --help Display this help information

-n, --name 'container name'

-r, --rel 'release-name'

-t, --type 'type-name' e.g. basic or dev.....

-V, --version Print script version information
EXIT STATUS
0 - Success

1 - General failure

64 - Error in command line
FILES
lxcu.conf  The script reads the configuration file to set default values.
